## Why I Study and Write Notes in LaTeX

---

### The Reasoning

I really disliked school, so much so that I coasted through most of high school without really studying. It was okay because I managed to get good enough grades to pass my classes. However, now at age 22, I deeply regret not applying myself more.

That being said, regret only holds power if you don't take action. My perspective on studying completely turned around when I was accepted into the ALX Software Engineering program. This incredible program aims to equip African citizens with the skills needed to thrive in the technology industry.

Upon being accepted, I faced a challenge—I didn't know how to study effectively. So, I started researching. I read books, articles, and watched videos, which motivated me to reassess my approach to studying.

### The Motivation

Here are the resources that had the greatest impact on me:

1. [Deep Work - Cal Newport](https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/25744928): Book resource
2. [Elon Musk - Ashlee Vance](https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/25541028): Book resource
3. [Jay Skullz](https://www.youtube.com/@jayskullz): Video resource
4. [Multivariable Calculus using Neovim + LaTeX - Neil Mehra](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-76tLYiqVY&t=2s): Video resource
5. [Senior Mars - Math Major using Vim + LaTeX](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DOtM1mrWjUo&t=254s): Video resource

#### [Deep Work - Cal Newport](https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/25744928)

This book provides great insights into how maximizing focus can enhance learning and productivity. If you're already sold on the concept of deep work, skip to the second part of the book.

#### [Elon Musk - Ashlee Vance](https://www.goodreads.com/en/book/show/25541028)

While not strictly about studying, this book showcases Elon Musk's drive and achievements. Musk's vision for the future is inspiring, beyond just his success as a businessman.

#### [Jay Skullz](https://www.youtube.com/@jayskullz)

Jay Skullz runs a great YouTube channel where he streams study sessions and shares his motivation for studying.

#### [Multivariable Calculus using Neovim + LaTeX - Neil Mehra](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=m-76tLYiqVY&t=2s)

This video demonstrates efficient LaTeX editing in Neovim, alongside a beautifully configured Neovim setup.

#### [Senior Mars - Math Major using Vim + LaTeX](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=DOtM1mrWjUo&t=254s)

This video first inspired me about using LaTeX for note-taking and studying. It's a great example of what's possible and provides insights into how to do it effectively.

### My Workflow

Currently, I balance a full-time job with studying. This limits the hours I can devote to deep work, but I manage to set aside a couple of hours daily.

I dedicate at least an hour each day to mathematics, essentially covering material from grade 9 to grade 12 due to my lack of prior study.

All my remaining free time goes into the ALX program, where we're gearing up for intensive C programming. To prepare, I read textbooks and take notes. I write all example programs in a dedicated folder alongside my notes, ready to be uploaded to GitHub. Additionally, I aim to solve at least 2 problems on [Code Chef](https://www.codechef.com/learn/dashboard) to keep my problem-solving skills sharp.

I used to devote time to studying Japanese as well, but that's currently on hold.

### Conclusion

While I may have neglected my studies earlier in life, that's no longer an excuse. I've found a study workflow that suits me well. Your approach may vary, but my advice is to find joy in your study process—I find great satisfaction in creating well-crafted notes.

